{"000-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Matsyakara Bharosa Scheme 2020 for Fishermen \u2013 Complete Details"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Andhra Pradesh govt. starts disbursement of Rs. 10k in AP YSR Matsyakara Bharosa Scheme 2020, increased financial assistance of Rs. 10,000 to fishermen operating mechanised, motorised, non-motorised fishing nets, hunting rafts, diesel subsidy of Rs. 9 per litre & enhanced ex-gratia of Rs. 10 lakh to died fishermen families"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "AP YSR Matsyakara Bharosa Scheme 2020", "001-normal": "The important features and highlights of this AP govt. scheme for fishermen are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- Increased assistance of Rs. 10,000 (previously Rs. 4,000) to fishermen amid COVID-19 lockdown.", "003-listElement": "- AP YSR Matsyakara Bharosa Scheme beneficiaries to get increased diesel subsidy of Rs. 9 per litre which was Rs. 6.03 earlier. AP govt. has identified 81 filing stations for this purpose.", "004-listElement": "- Earlier, financial assistance was only given to those fishermen who uses mechanised and motorized boats. But the current dispensation would extend benefits to even those fishermen who uses hunting rafts.", "005-listElement": "- A total number of 1.09 lakh families of fishermen would be benefited from AP YSR Matsyakara Nestham Scheme.", "006-listElement": "- Furthermore, ex-gratia provided to fishermen families which died while hunting has been raised from Rs. 5 lakh to Rs. 10 lakh. All the fishermen in 18 to 60 years of age group can avail this benefit.", "007-normal": "CM YS Jagan Mohan Reddy announced enhancement of benefits after reviewing the miserable conditions of fishermen during his 3,648 km-long padayatra.", "008-normal": "All the beneficiaries are rejoicing and expressed their pleasure as the unprecedented aid of Rs. 10,000 comes from AP govt. during Coronavirus lockdown."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "Other Benefits for Fishermen in AP", "001-normal": "AP govt. will setup Integrated aqua labs in 46 locations at Rs. 56.53 crore. These labs are going to test quality of water, sand, feed and seeds for the benefit of aquaculturists.", "002-normal": "AP govt. has also allocated Rs. 720 crore to provide power to aqua farmers at cost of Rs. 1.5 per unit to benefit around 53,550 farmers. Other major decisions are to provide rights to fishermen on canals on lease at a nominal cost and provision of input subsidy.", "003-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://www.thehansindia.com/andhra-pradesh/andhra-govt-begins-disbursement-rs-10000-to-fishermen-under-ysr-matsyakara-bharosa-scheme-621042"}}